On behalf of National Library Board, we are looking for 60 Casual Staff to be deployed when libraries resume operations.&nbsp;

Crowd Control, Temperature Screening and Registration Management

  Report at working station (located at identified entrance to the library) at least 5 minutes before start of each shift.
  Assist in crowd/queue management and carry out temperature screening checks on all visitors at the entrance to the library.
  Disallow visitors who have a temperature of 38 degrees or above to enter the library
  Assist visitors with scanning of QR code for contact tracing purpose (SafeEntry).
  Any safe-distancing measures duties as assigned.
  Shift work (Up to 4 days per week)
  10am - 9pm
